States%20Going%20To%20Polls%20On%20Friday%2C%20Experts%20Fear%20Drop%20In%20Turnout%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20BJP%20eyes%20a%20third%20consecutive%20term%20and%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20tries%20its%20best%20to%20stop%20it%20from%20doing%20so%2C%20parties%20and%20voters%20are%20not%20only%20having%20to%20contend%20with%20rising%20political%20temperatures%20but%20also%20a%20heatwave%20sweeping%20many%20states%2C%20which%20is%20seen%20to%20have%20impacted%20the%20turnout%20in%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20voter%20turnout%20for%20the%20first%20and%20biggest%20phase%20of%20the%20general%20elections%20settled%20at%2065.5%25%2C%20a%20drop%20of%204.4%20percentage%20points%20from%20the%2069.9%25%20seen%20in%20the%20same%20constituencies%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2013%20states%20and%20Union%20Territories%20are%20going%20to%20the%20polls%20in%20the%20second%20phase%20of%20Friday%20and%20what%20has%20got%20experts%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Election%20Commission%20worried%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20heatwave%20warning%20for%20parts%20of%20at%20least%20four%20such%20states%20-%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Karnataka%20-%20on%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20from%20Bihar's%20Nawada%20and%20Gaya%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20backs%20the%20hypothesis%20that%20higher%20temperatures%2C%20especially%20over%2040%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20voter%20turnout.%20On%20April%2011%2C%202019%2C%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20was%2035%20degrees%20C%20in%20Nawada%20and%20the%20turnout%20was%2052.5%25%3B%20this%20dropped%20to%20just%2041.5%25%20on%20April%2019%2C%20when%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20was%2042%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Gaya%2C%20the%20turnout%20was%2056%25%20on%20April%2011%2C%202019%2C%20when%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20was%2035%20degrees%20C%2C%20dropping%20to%2052%25%20last%20Friday%2C%20when%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20was%2042.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20has%20forecast%20a%20hot%20summer%2C%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20heatwave%20days.%20With%20six%20phases%20of%20polling%20still%20left%2C%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20and%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20held%20a%20high-level%20meeting%2C%20which%20was%20attended%20by%20the%20IMD%20chief%2C%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20meeting%20is%20also%20planned%20with%20Chief%20Electoral%20Officers%20of%20the%20states%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20necessary%20facilities%20like%20awnings%2C%20drinking%20water%20and%20fans%20at%20all%20polling%20stations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStates%20Affected%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Naresh%20Kumar%2C%20Senior%20Scientist%20at%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%2C%20told%20NDTV%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20issued%20a%20red%20alert%20for%20heat%20in%20West%20Bengal%20for%20the%20next%20three%20days.%20Temperatures%20in%20Bihar%20will%20exceed%2040%20degrees%20Celsius.%20A%20heatwave%20is%20expected%20in%20eastern%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20after%2024%20hours%20and%20in%20western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20after%20two%20days.%20The%20temperature%20will%20remain%20hot%20and%20humid%20in%20Kerala%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heat%20will%20be%20even%20more%20of%20a%20challenge%20in%20Ghaziabad%20in%20western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20has%20seen%20a%20low%20voter%20turnout%20in%20successive%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20what%20was%20being%20done%20to%20tackle%20this%2C%20Abhinav%20Gopal%2C%20Chief%20Development%20Officer%2C%20Ghaziabad%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAdequate%20arrangements%20for%20drinking%20water%20are%20being%20made%20in%20every%20polling%20booth.%20We%20have%20done%20the%20mapping.%20Wherever%20this%20problem%20can%20occur%2C%20tents%20and%20other%20areas%20with%20shade%20are%20being%20set%20up%20so%20people%20can%20get%20a%20reprieve%20from%20the%20heat.%20Polling%20booths%20have%20also%20been%20set%20up%20in%20complexes%20so%20voters%20don't%20have%20to%20travel%20too%20far.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Can%20Voters%20Do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Kumar%20from%20the%20IMD%20said%20voters%20can%20also%20take%20steps%20to%20keep%20themselves%20safe%20and%20hydrated.%20%26quot%3BAccording%20to%20the%20guidelines%20issued%20by%20the%20National%20Disaster%20Management%20Authority%2C%20people%20should%20wear%20light-coloured%2C%20loose-fitting%20clothes%20and%20cover%20the%20head%20with%20a%20cap%20or%20cloth.%20They%20should%20keep%20themselves%20covered%20and%20not%20expose%20too%20much%20of%20the%20body%20to%20the%20heat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlways%20carry%20plenty%20of%20fluids%20and%20water%2C%20and%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20daily%20forecast%20as%20well%20as%20advisories%20of%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713873360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fkiopm9e_voting-heat_625x300_23_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fheatwave-in-4-states-going-to-polls-on-friday-experts-fear-drop-in-turnout-5505558%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20BJP%20eyes%20a%20third%20consecutive%20term%20and%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20tries%20its%20best%20to%20stop%20it%20from%20doing%20so%2C%20parties%20and%20voters%20are%20not%20only%20having%20to%20contend%20with%20rising%20political%20temperatures%20but%20also%20a%20heatwave%20sweeping%20many%20states.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fheatwave-in-4-states-going-to-polls-on-friday-experts-fear-drop-in-turnout-5505558%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fheatwave-in-4-states-going-to-polls-on-friday-experts-fear-drop-in